                                                <p><strong>Introduction:</strong></p>
                                                <p>The line graph illustrates the changes in the number of tourists visiting Thailand between 2010 and 2020.</p>

                                                <p><strong>Overview:</strong></p>
                                                <p>Overall, there was a significant increase in tourist numbers over the period, with the highest figure recorded in 2019.</p>

                                                <p><strong>Body Paragraph 1:</strong></p>
                                                <p>In 2010, approximately 15 million tourists visited Thailand. This number gradually increased to around 20 million in 2015. However, there was a slight decrease in 2016, dropping to about 18 million visitors.</p>

                                                <p><strong>Body Paragraph 2:</strong></p>
                                                <p>From 2017 onwards, tourist numbers rose dramatically, reaching a peak of 35 million in 2019. However, in 2020, there was a sharp decline to approximately 10 million tourists, likely due to the global pandemic.</p>
                                            </div>
